        "title": "How to register irregular-class beans by hand in Spring",
        "body": "<p>For regular class which has regular fields with regular <strong>getters<\/strong> and <strong>setters<\/strong>, Spring's <code>BeanDefinitionBuilder<\/code> and <code>BeanDefinition<\/code> work well.<\/p>\n\n<p>But for those irregular class (e.g., the class using builder-mode creation), Spring will fail to load these beans due to there is no <strong>setter<\/strong> function in the class.<\/p>\n\n<p>The <code>beanFactory.registerSingleton()<\/code> can not suit because I want to register many Objects with the same Class and different names.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 50549068,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "spring"
        ],
